Modes on router

User execution mode - Monitoring purpose
Privilege mode - Troubleshooting purpose, running-config,statrup-config, show access list
Global configuration mode - config router globally such as, NAT,ACL, Routing
Interface configuration mode - Config only to specific interface, such as set IP, Mac, duplex, speed.
Rommon mode - Used for Restore the IOS from TFTP server and Reverting the password.

Symbols to identify the modes of router

Router > User execution mode
Router # Privilege mode
Router (config) # Global configuration mode
Router (config-if) # Interface configuration mode
rommon 1 > Rommon mode

