## 1. The Hardware: PC, Switch (SW), and Router## PC (End Device)

* Definition: The source or destination of data.
* OSI Level: Layer 1–7 (Full Stack).
* Config: Needs IP, Subnet Mask, and Default Gateway.
* Real-Time Example: Your laptop accessing a website.

## Switch (Layer 2)

* Definition: Connects devices within the same local network (LAN) using MAC addresses.
* OSI Level: Layer 2 (Data Link).
* Working Process: Learns MAC addresses and puts them in a MAC Table.
* Configuration:

int vlan 1
ip address 192.168.1.2 255.255.255.0
no shut
ip default-gateway 192.168.1.1


## Router (Layer 3)

* Definition: Connects different networks (LAN to WAN) using IP addresses.
* OSI Level: Layer 3 (Network).
* Working Process: Uses a Routing Table to find the best path for packets.
* Configuration:

interface g0/0
ip address 192.168.1.1 255.255.255.0
no shut


