## 2. ARP & GARP (The Address Finders)## ARP (Address Resolution Protocol)

* Definition: Maps a known IP address to an unknown MAC address.
* OSI Level: Layer 2.5 (Works between L2 and L3).
* Working Process:
1. Request: Broadcast ("Who is 10.1?").
   2. Reply: Unicast ("I am 10.1, here is my MAC").
* Real-Time Example: Your PC needs to send data to the router but doesn't know the router’s MAC yet.

## GARP (Gratuitous ARP)

* Definition: An "unasked" ARP reply sent by a device to announce itself.
* Working Process: Shouts its own IP/MAC to the network.
* Real-Time Example: Detecting IP conflicts when you plug in a new PC.

