## 3. Telnet & SSH (Remote Management)## Telnet

* Definition: A protocol for remote CLI access. Insecure (Plain text).
* Port Number: 23 (TCP).
* OSI Level: Layer 7 (Application).
* Configuration:

line vty 0 4
password cisco
login


## SSH (Secure Shell)

* Definition: Secure, encrypted remote CLI access.
* Port Number: 22 (TCP).
* OSI Level: Layer 7 (Application).
* Configuration:

hostname R1
ip domain-name lab.com
crypto key generate rsa (choose 1024)
username admin password cisco
line vty 0 4
login local
transport input ssh


